(SELECT "version" FROM finance.forecast_data_new WHERE "version"!='Actuals' ORDER BY CAST(SPLIT_PART("version",'+',1) AS INTEGER) DESC LIMIT 1)

PRIOR version subquery:
(SELECT "version" FROM finance.forecast_data_new WHERE "version"!='Actuals' ORDER BY CAST(SPLIT_PART("version",'+',1) AS INTEGER) DESC LIMIT 1 OFFSET 1)

VERSION COMPARISON — mandatory CASE WHEN pattern:
SUM(CASE WHEN "version"='2+10' THEN COALESCE("amount",0) ELSE 0 END) AS "latest"
SUM(CASE WHEN "version"='1+11' THEN COALESCE("amount",0) ELSE 0 END) AS "previous"
variance = latest - previous
variance_pct = variance / NULLIF(previous,0) * 100
Column order ALWAYS: group-by col, latest, previous, variance, variance_pct.
ORDER BY ABS(variance) DESC for comparisons.
ONLY generate comparison when user says "compare","vs","variance","difference". Otherwise single version only.

DYNAMIC VERSION (not stated):
latest = LATEST version subquery above
prior = PRIOR version subquery above
